			<h3>Summary:</h3><br/>
			<p>"The Daily Life of High School Boys" is an anime series that revolves around the daily lives of three high school boys, Tadakuni, Yoshitake, and Hidenori. This slice-of-life comedy series takes a humorous approach to the everyday experiences of high school boys, from mundane activities like going to class to more adventurous endeavours like going on a school trip.</p>

			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/4.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>
            <p>The characters are well-developed, and each has a distinct personality, making them relatable and entertaining. Tadakuni is the group's straight man, often reacting to the absurd situations that Yoshitake and Hidenori get themselves into. Yoshitake is the carefree and laid-back one who always seems up for anything, while Hidenori is the mischievous one who likes to stir things up.</p>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/5.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/6.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>

			<h3>The Main Characters:</h3><br/>
            <ul>
			<li><h4>Hidenori</h4></br>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/7.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>
            <p>The trio's leader is often the most level-headed and rational of the group. He is also highly imaginative and prone to daydreaming.</p>
			</li>
            <li>
            <h4>Yoshitake</h4></br>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/8.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>
            <p>The goofball of the group, and often acts on impulse without thinking things through. He is also highly energetic and has a great sense of humour.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
			<h4>Tadakuni</h4></br>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/9.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>
            <p>The actual main character, but there are a few episodes where Tadakuni isn’t even mentioned. The most reserved of the trio, and often serves as the voice of reason. He is also highly introspective and thoughtful.</p>
            </li>
            <p></br>Each character in "The Daily Life of High School Boys" brings something unique to the show, and their different personalities and quirks help to create a well-rounded and entertaining cast of characters.</p>
            <br/>
            <h3>Why even bother watching this?</h3><br/>
			<p>The humour in the show is top-notch, relying heavily on witty banter, pop culture references, and hilarious visual gags. The writing is clever and keeps the jokes fresh and unpredictable, making it a joy to watch from start to finish.</p>
            <p>What sets this series apart from other high school comedies is its ability to tackle serious topics in a lighthearted way. The show addresses issues such as bullying, peer pressure, and social anxiety, but never loses its comedic edge.</p>
            </br>
            <h3>Animation:</h3><br/>
			<p>The animation style is simple yet effective, with a colorful and vibrant color palette that adds to the overall cheerful tone of the series. The music is also catchy and memorable, perfectly complementing the upbeat and energetic vibe of the show.</p>
			<br/><center><img src="/assets/releases/2023-04-1/10.gif" style="max-height: 35vh; max-width: 70%; display: block;"></center><br/>           
            </br>
            <h3>Conclusion: </h3><br/>
            <p>Overall, "The Daily Life of High School Boys" is a must-watch for fans of slice-of-life comedies. Its witty writing, lovable characters, and clever humour make it a standout in the genre and a truly enjoyable viewing experience. It will remind you of friends from your high school days, and make you reminisce of the times you spent with them. (All aboard the feels train. (┬┬﹏┬┬) ) Even if you were a loner, you will still find this show relatable somehow.</p>
            <p>10/10 in all aspects from me.</p>
